        <title>Congressionally Mandated Reports - New items on GovInfo</title>
        <link>https://www.govinfo.gov/app/collection/cmr</link>
        <description>Provides access to newly published GovInfo content from the  Congressionally Mandated Reports. Federal agencies are required by statute to routinely transmit reports, notifications, studies, and other information, which are known as “congressionally mandated reports”, to either House of Congress or any committee of Congress or subcommittee on a specified timeline. On December 23, 2022, Public Law 117-263, the James M. Inhofe National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2023 (H.R. 117-7776), was signed into law. This law requires that the GPO Director establish and maintain an online portal accessible by the public that allows the ability for anyone to obtain electronic copies of congressionally mandated reports in one place.</description>
